article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 60, Cal Poly-SLO 47
article.story: SANTA BARBARA (AP) -- Alex Harris scored 19 of his 21 points in the final 25 minutes to help UC Santa Barbara rally for a 60-47 victory over Cal Poly Thursday night. The Gauchos (18-6, 7-4 Big West Conference) trailed 19-17 after Trae Clark's 3-pointer. He led the Mustangs (9-14, 4-7) with 14 points and five assists. But Harris scored nine points in the last five minutes of the half to put UCSB ahead 31-25. Chris Devine scored six straight points midway through the second half to boost the Gauchos' lead to 53-43. He finished with 16 points. UCSB held Cal Poly to 34.8 percent shooting and forced 24 turnovers while making a season-high 16 steals.
